Metmar Climbs Most in Five Months After Saying Headline Earnings Increased

-- B y   V e r n o n   W e s s e l s
-- 
2011-03-22T10:37:07Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-22/metmar-climbs-most-in-five-months-after-saying-headline-earnings-increased.html
Metmar Ltd. (MML) , a South African mining
investment company, gained the most in five months after saying
that fiscal full-year earnings per share before one-time items
increased by as much as 76 percent.  The stock increased by 24 cents, or 6.5 percent, the
biggest intraday jump since Oct. 24, to 3.94 rand.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Vernon Wessels at 
 vwessels@bloomberg.net  